<h3>Broken Ignitor in Gas Ovens:</h3>
<p>If the ignitor fails to produce a spark, the oven won't heat up as needed. Identifying a broken ignitor may require a multimeter test, making it advisable to call a repair technician. Professional appliance repair technicians possess the expertise and tools to quickly identify and address the issue.</p>
